253
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:38,781
Why is it so smoky?

254
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:41,325
Oh God, the popcorn!

255
00:11:42,702 --> 00:11:44,995
Enjoying yourselves, kids?

256
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:48,040
You're upstairs people now.

257
00:11:49,417 --> 00:11:50,918
I knew it would happen.

258
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:52,753
Just not this soon.

259
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:57,049
Quit worrying, Eric. Leia will be fine.

260
00:11:57,758 --> 00:11:59,343
So now you can tell the future?

261
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:01,929
Where were you when I bought
those slippery brown shoes?

262
00:12:02,012 --> 00:12:03,931
I couldn't get up the ramp at the airport.

263
00:12:04,014 --> 00:12:05,099
[Donna] Okay, Eric.

264
00:12:08,144 --> 00:12:09,395
No more Zima for you.

265
00:12:10,604 --> 00:12:12,898
Yeah, you're right. I'm… I'm flying.

266
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:15,609
I saved most of it.

267
00:12:15,693 --> 00:12:16,861
Ah. Thanks, Mom.

268
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:18,654
"Mom."

269
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,157
You see how easy it is, Donna?

270
00:12:22,742 --> 00:12:24,744
Can't you just say it?

271
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:27,830
Nah. Feels forced.

272
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:30,082
Come on, Mom, just drop it.

273
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:31,876
Nah.

274
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:33,586
Feels forced.

275
00:12:37,006 --> 00:12:40,176
[rock music playing]

276
00:12:41,093 --> 00:12:42,344
Kids versus beer.

277
00:12:43,095 --> 00:12:44,722
It's a tale as old as time.

278
00:12:45,306 --> 00:12:48,809
It happened to our parents
and our parents' parents.

279
00:12:48,893 --> 00:12:50,269
The kids on the Mayflower.

280
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:54,356
Ozzie. You're killing me, man.
I'm trying to think here.

281
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:56,484
I know. I can smell it.

282
00:12:57,818 --> 00:13:01,530
Wait, why can't we just
go back to Mama's and get a tap?

283
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:04,658
We've all tried to buy from her,
but she's tough.

284
00:13:04,742 --> 00:13:06,702
I mean, I even hit her with the,

285
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,121
"Hey, girl."

286
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:10,873
Nothing.

287
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:15,127
-What if we get a laser?
-We're not getting a laser.

288
00:13:16,086 --> 00:13:18,214
Well, I guess that's it.
We tried everything.

289
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:20,549
You said one idea, and it was stupid.

290
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:21,592
You're stupid!

291
00:13:21,675 --> 00:13:24,595
You're all stupid!
You hate beer and you hate America.

292
00:13:24,678 --> 00:13:25,971
-Baby?
-Yeah?

293
00:13:26,055 --> 00:13:27,556
Are you feeling frustrated?

294
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:28,474
Yeah.

295
00:13:28,557 --> 00:13:31,894
-Is this why you're lashing out at others?
-Yeah.

296
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:37,525
How about tomorrow we go into the woods,
and I watch you do karate on a tree?

297
00:13:37,608 --> 00:13:38,859
-I'd really like that.
-Oh.

298
00:13:40,528 --> 00:13:41,987
Are you dill weeds finished?

299
00:13:42,071 --> 00:13:45,324
Leia, you should buy the tap.
Mama doesn't know you.

300
00:13:45,407 --> 00:13:47,201
Oh yeah. You totally could.

301
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:50,120
Plus, your eyes are crazy pretty,
which won't really help get the tap,

302
00:13:50,204 --> 00:13:51,789
but it's something I noticed.

303
00:13:53,207 --> 00:13:54,750
-Hey, girl.
-[scoffs]

304
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:58,587
Leia, it would be so badass.

305
00:13:59,171 --> 00:14:01,340
I guess I have done
some pretty crazy things.

306
00:14:01,423 --> 00:14:04,301
One time at the beach,
a seagull stole my sandwich,

307
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:08,055
and, under my breath,
I… called her "bitch."

308
00:14:10,891 --> 00:14:12,309
You know what? I'm in.

309
00:14:12,893 --> 00:14:14,478
All right. New girl is sick.

310
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:16,105
-To the van!
-Pause.

311
00:14:17,398 --> 00:14:18,774
This isn't gonna work.

312
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:21,443
I'm pretty sure OshKosh B'gosh here
is gonna get carded.

313
00:14:22,987 --> 00:14:23,988
Good point.

314
00:14:25,072 --> 00:14:26,073
I have an idea.

315
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:33,956
You sure you want to be drinking
in your condition, hon?

316
00:14:34,039 --> 00:14:35,457
Oh, it's… [nervous chuckle]

317
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:38,961
It's for my husband.
He… He got a keg for the baby shower.

318
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:41,380
Oh, fancy.

319
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:43,549
[register beeping]

320
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:45,968
-That'll be $39.50.
-Okay.

321
00:14:50,014 --> 00:14:53,559
I'm no lady doctor, but I think
something's wrong with the baby.

322
00:14:55,352 --> 00:14:56,186
Nice try.

323
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:58,480
I'm sick of you kids.
I'm calling the cops.

324
00:14:59,523 --> 00:15:01,483
Put the phone down, Mama.

325
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:02,693
Shut up.

326
00:15:02,776 --> 00:15:04,570
Fine, but when the cops get here,

327
00:15:04,653 --> 00:15:08,240
how are you gonna explain to them
why you gave a keg to a bunch of kids?

328
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:09,909
It wasn't me. It was Wade.

329
00:15:09,992 --> 00:15:10,868
Mama!

330
00:15:12,828 --> 00:15:15,539
Either way, you lose your liquor license.

331
00:15:15,623 --> 00:15:20,961
So put the phone down, sell me the tap,
and we all have a nice Fourth of July.

332
00:15:24,214 --> 00:15:26,050
What are you, some sort of lawyer?

333
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:29,303
Debate Club.
First place, junior regionals.

334
00:15:29,386 --> 00:15:31,013
It was over before it started.

335
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,389
[gasps]

336
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:36,602
[rock music playing]

337
00:15:36,685 --> 00:15:39,313
To Leia, the Mama slayer!

338
00:15:39,396 --> 00:15:40,773
[all] To Leia!

339
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:43,317
And to Mrs. Zapolski. [chuckles]

340
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:46,111
My Debate Club coach,
for pushing me so damn hard.

341
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:48,489
[all] To Mrs. Zapolski!

342
00:15:49,698 --> 00:15:53,327
Wow. Look, Nik, a shooting star.
Make a wish.

343
00:15:53,410 --> 00:15:54,745
That's a firework, babe.

344
00:15:54,828 --> 00:15:56,121
[fireworks whistling and popping]

345
00:15:56,205 --> 00:15:59,792
Man, you were such a badass tonight.
I didn't know you had it in you.

346
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:04,254
Neither did I, but I love this feeling.

347
00:16:04,338 --> 00:16:08,968
I feel free and happy.
Wish I could stay for the summer.

348
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:11,136
Then stay.

349
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:13,305
[snickers] My dad will never let me.

350
00:16:14,014 --> 00:16:15,599
When my parents split up,

351
00:16:15,683 --> 00:16:19,478
the school shrink basically told me
that everything was gonna suck forever,

352
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:23,357
and I was like, "Nope. Not this girl."

353
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:26,402
So I went home, bleached my hair
over the washing machine,

354
00:16:26,485 --> 00:16:29,071
cut up my jeans
and decided that this is <i>my</i> life,

355
00:16:29,154 --> 00:16:30,489
and it's <i>never </i>gonna suck.

356
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:34,827
This is gonna sound so dorky,

357
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:38,247
but… I'm interested in
us becoming best friends,

358
00:16:38,330 --> 00:16:39,707
so how do we make that happen?

359
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:41,792
Stay for the summer.

360
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:45,337
And you can drop the dorky disclaimer.
It's implied.

361
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:46,380
[chuckles]

362
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:48,257
Oh great.

363
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:50,968
Now she's missed the fireworks
and the weenies.

364
00:16:51,051 --> 00:16:55,305
Now they're sitting on a plate
all cold and shriveled just like my heart.

365
00:16:55,806 --> 00:16:57,933
Oh, Eric.

366
00:16:58,017 --> 00:17:00,269
The hair thing,
it's still a little weird, Mom.

367
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:03,355
Know what the worst part is?
I should be treasuring time with Leia.

368
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:06,066
Instead, I mean,
I… can't wait for it to end.

369
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:07,985
Oh, sweetie.

370
00:17:08,068 --> 00:17:09,987
It ends when you die.

371
00:17:13,532 --> 00:17:15,784
Leia Tatooine Forman.

372
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:19,329
-Her middle name is Anne.
-Know what? I never agreed to that.

373
00:17:19,830 --> 00:17:22,332
Where have you been?
Oh my God. Is that beer?

374
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:25,419
Yeah. And I spilled the rest
coming down the water tower.

375
00:17:25,502 --> 00:17:27,671
The… water tower? What the hell?

376
00:17:27,755 --> 00:17:29,089
Eric, let me handle this.

377
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:30,799
The water tower? What the hell?

378
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:33,302
Now, this is <i>my </i>kind of fireworks.

379
00:17:35,637 --> 00:17:37,097
Yes, the water tower.

380
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:40,017
And I had a great time
and I don't want it to end.

381
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:42,394
So I know you're not
gonna like me saying this,

382
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:44,980
but… I want to stay in Point Place
for the summer.

383
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:47,983
This is my life,
and I'm done letting it suck.

384
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:49,276
-Leia.
-Yeah, go.

385
00:17:49,359 --> 00:17:51,403
Just unload, baby. Both barrels. Go.

386
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:55,032
-That took courage. I'm impressed.
-What?!

387
00:17:55,115 --> 00:17:56,950
Th-This is a ridiculous idea.

388
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:59,369
-Leia.
-Mom, just go, preach.

389
00:17:59,453 --> 00:18:02,498
You are welcome to stay here
if that's what you want.

390
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:04,249
Oh my God! What's happening?

391
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:05,167
Kitty.

392
00:18:06,585 --> 00:18:08,712
I guess that's what we want.

393
00:18:11,381 --> 00:18:13,133
Dad, you guys always talk about

394
00:18:13,217 --> 00:18:15,219
the amazing times
you had with your friends.

395
00:18:15,302 --> 00:18:17,262
I want that. I want amazing.

396
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:19,264
Listen, pal. In the space of one day,

397
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:22,017
you've gotten pierced, you've gotten beer,
and you've gotten

398
00:18:22,643 --> 00:18:24,311
extremely snippy.

399
00:18:24,978 --> 00:18:27,272
You've turned into someone
that I don't know anymore.

400
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:29,024
So no. You know what? You can forget it.

401
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:30,859
I knew you were gonna be like this.

402
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:32,903
I'm not getting in that car tomorrow!
You can't make me!

403
00:18:32,986 --> 00:18:35,614
Oh, you're getting in that car
or my foot is getting in your ass!

404
00:18:38,826 --> 00:18:41,620
-Oh, Eric.
-So bad.

405
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:45,207
I have never been prouder.

406
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:50,170
It's like watching you hit
your first home run.

407
00:18:51,296 --> 00:18:52,589
If you had ever done that.

408
00:18:53,674 --> 00:18:57,344
[soft guitar music playing]

409
00:18:57,427 --> 00:18:59,263
[crickets chirping]

410
00:19:01,181 --> 00:19:02,182
You okay?

411
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,393
I can't believe it.

412
00:19:04,476 --> 00:19:07,187
I study <i>Star Wars</i> my entire life,
and in my moment of truth,

413
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:09,523
I turn into my evil father.

414
00:19:12,818 --> 00:19:13,986
I've thought about it.

415
00:19:14,486 --> 00:19:17,781
Leia staying isn't the craziest idea.
Your parents can watch her.

416
00:19:17,865 --> 00:19:19,700
Were you not here with me in the '70s?

417
00:19:19,783 --> 00:19:21,410
They are not the best watchers.

418
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:23,662
She's a great kid.

419
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:26,832
Yeah, I know.

420
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:28,167
We can trust her.

421
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:29,293
I know.

422
00:19:29,793 --> 00:19:31,044
So what, then?

423
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,296
I just…

424
00:19:32,379 --> 00:19:35,174
I mean, I can't stand this feeling.
She doesn't need me anymore.

425
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:38,510
I mean, she was my little buddy,
and now she's like

426
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:40,596
a stranger.

427
00:19:40,679 --> 00:19:44,308
She's not a stranger.
She's just… growing up.

428
00:19:45,726 --> 00:19:46,560
I don't like it.

429
00:19:46,643 --> 00:19:49,688
What? But you're so good
at hiding your emotions.

430
00:19:49,771 --> 00:19:51,023
[both chuckle]

431
00:19:52,983 --> 00:19:54,610
Eric, it's gonna be okay.

432
00:19:55,777 --> 00:19:56,820
We have our whole lives

433
00:19:56,904 --> 00:19:59,323
because your parents
gave us the space to find each other.

434
00:20:01,408 --> 00:20:02,409
Really?

435
00:20:02,492 --> 00:20:05,913
You lived 20 feet away. I'm pretty sure
we would have found each other.

436
00:20:07,706 --> 00:20:10,792
[soft guitar music playing]

437
00:20:19,801 --> 00:20:20,802
Hey.

438
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:22,638
What?

439
00:20:23,347 --> 00:20:25,891
-Oh, what happened to the nose ring?
-It was a magnet.

440
00:20:25,974 --> 00:20:27,976
I sneezed and it went down the drain.

441
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:29,061
Ah.

442
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:31,980
Well, I'm… I'm heartbroken.

443
00:20:33,273 --> 00:20:34,399
Back when I was your age,

444
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:36,860
my friends and I pretty much
lived down in this basement.

445
00:20:36,944 --> 00:20:41,073
We'd kill time, listen to music,
do… other things.

446
00:20:42,449 --> 00:20:46,119
Sitting on those stairs right there
when I fell in love with your mom.

447
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:49,456
Oh God. Did you do it on those stairs too?

448
00:20:49,539 --> 00:20:50,499
No.

449
00:20:53,877 --> 00:20:54,878
No.

450
00:20:56,713 --> 00:20:58,757
Look, I've been thinking about it, and…

451
00:21:01,343 --> 00:21:03,303
You should stay… for the summer.

452
00:21:04,805 --> 00:21:06,473
-Are you for real?
-Yeah.

453
00:21:07,224 --> 00:21:11,395
If anyone deserves some… amazing,
it's you.

454
00:21:11,979 --> 00:21:15,774
Oh my God, Dad. Thank you.
Sorry I was kind of a jerk.

455
00:21:15,857 --> 00:21:18,151
Well, you were
surprisingly good at it. [chuckles]

456
00:21:19,486 --> 00:21:20,737
But, you know, you're…

457
00:21:22,698 --> 00:21:23,699
You're good at everything.

458
00:21:27,703 --> 00:21:28,829
I'll miss you, pal.

459
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:31,581
I love you so much, okay?

460
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:34,334
[sighs softly]

461
00:21:34,418 --> 00:21:36,003
Are you smelling my hair?

462
00:21:36,086 --> 00:21:37,421
No.

463
00:21:38,505 --> 00:21:40,632
'Cause that would be weird.

464
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:43,677
[sniffs] Okay.

465
00:21:44,219 --> 00:21:47,556
[soft rock music playing]

466
00:21:50,851 --> 00:21:54,062
So just remember
our phone number hasn't changed, okay?

467
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:57,774
Don't worry, honey. I got it.

468
00:21:58,400 --> 00:21:59,234
Again.

469
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:01,570
Okay, babe.

470
00:22:03,405 --> 00:22:05,073
My baby boy.

471
00:22:05,574 --> 00:22:07,909
Oh, uh… Mom.

472
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:09,745
Shh!

473
00:22:09,828 --> 00:22:11,872
I'm listening to your heartbeat.

474
00:22:13,165 --> 00:22:14,166
Look. Okay.

475
00:22:19,713 --> 00:22:20,881
[Donna coos]

476
00:22:21,715 --> 00:22:22,632
Love you, Le-Le.

477
00:22:22,716 --> 00:22:23,633
Bye, Mom.

478
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:27,888
Don't worry. We're gonna have fun.

479
00:22:27,971 --> 00:22:29,306
You ever cleaned an oven?

480
00:22:30,432 --> 00:22:31,433
Good luck.

481
00:22:32,309 --> 00:22:35,187
And one more thing, Leia.
This one's… really important.

482
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:38,607
With your new friends, I want you
to hang out in Grandpa's basement

483
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:40,192
as much as possible.

484
00:22:40,275 --> 00:22:42,361
No. Uh-uh. No way.

485
00:22:42,444 --> 00:22:44,154
It is the safest place for her.

486
00:22:44,237 --> 00:22:47,240
That's right, Mom. That's so right.

487
00:22:47,324 --> 00:22:48,950
Nicely played, son.

488
00:22:49,034 --> 00:22:50,327
I learned from the best.

489
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:51,870
Nobody likes an ass-kisser.

490
00:22:54,206 --> 00:22:55,123
I love you too, Dad.

491
00:22:57,584 --> 00:22:58,585
Bye, Mom.

492
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:03,215
She said "Mom."

493
00:23:05,175 --> 00:23:06,343
I win.

494
00:23:07,511 --> 00:23:09,721
That's why you don't mess with a pro.

495
00:23:10,806 --> 00:23:15,143
[rock music playing]

496
00:23:15,227 --> 00:23:17,771
Well, I have to make a shopping list.

497
00:23:17,854 --> 00:23:19,606
The kids are gonna want snacks.

498
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:21,441
Don't feed them, Kitty.

499
00:23:21,525 --> 00:23:23,819
That's how it started the first time.

500
00:23:24,403 --> 00:23:26,571
Hey. Me and my friends
are going up to the lake.

501
00:23:26,655 --> 00:23:27,489
[Red] Hold on.

502
00:23:28,281 --> 00:23:30,117
-Who are you?
-I'm Jay.

503
00:23:31,576 --> 00:23:32,953
-Jay Kelso.
-No!

504
00:23:33,912 --> 00:23:35,038
Uh-uh!

505
00:23:35,122 --> 00:23:36,164
No way!

506
00:23:36,248 --> 00:23:38,375
Buuuurn!

507
00:23:42,295 --> 00:23:43,296
Ahh!

508
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:45,757
See you met my boy here, huh?
Look at this guy. Look at him.

509
00:23:45,841 --> 00:23:48,301
Look, he's got his dad's looks
and his mom's brains.

510
00:23:48,385 --> 00:23:49,719
Straight A's last year.

511
00:23:49,803 --> 00:23:51,888
Sweet Lord, it's evolving.

512
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:53,014
[Kelso chuckles]

513
00:23:53,807 --> 00:23:55,809
Hey, you kids. You have fun now, okay?

514
00:23:55,892 --> 00:23:58,061
Oh, and if you jump off that cliff,

515
00:23:58,145 --> 00:23:59,187
do it naked.

516
00:23:59,271 --> 00:24:01,731
Okay? 'Cause when you hit the water
at the right angle,

517
00:24:01,815 --> 00:24:03,275
it's like doing it with a lake.

518
00:24:07,654 --> 00:24:08,697
Hello, Michael.

519
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:09,656
Hey, girl.

520
00:24:09,739 --> 00:24:11,491
[Kitty giggles]

521
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:13,285
Beautiful! [yells, laughs]

522
00:24:13,368 --> 00:24:14,661
[Kitty laughs]

523
00:24:15,912 --> 00:24:19,666
-Well, that felt… toned and warm.
-[Kelso] Oh.

524
00:24:21,084 --> 00:24:21,918
So, Red,

525
00:24:22,502 --> 00:24:25,672
we need to talk about your granddaughter's
intentions with my boy.

526
00:24:27,174 --> 00:24:29,801
No, I'm just kidding ya.
Come on. Let's hug it out.

527
00:24:29,885 --> 00:24:31,136
What do you think?

528
00:24:32,012 --> 00:24:33,472
Michael, let's go!

529
00:24:35,056 --> 00:24:35,974
Hi, Kitty.

530
00:24:37,017 --> 00:24:40,020
Damn, Jackie, will you just
give me a minute to enjoy this?

531
00:24:40,103 --> 00:24:41,021
Oh my God.

532
00:24:41,521 --> 00:24:44,107
The vein on Red's forehead
is about to explode.

533
00:24:45,484 --> 00:24:49,488
Gross! I don't want old guy blood
all over my wedding outfit.

534
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:50,906
You're getting married?

535
00:24:50,989 --> 00:24:52,407
Remarried.

536
00:24:52,491 --> 00:24:54,409
-Yeah, it's our second remarriage.
-Mm-hmm.

537
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:57,537
-This one's gonna stick, right?
-Yeah.

538
00:24:59,372 --> 00:25:00,707
Jackie.

539
00:25:00,790 --> 00:25:01,958
White, honey?

540
00:25:03,668 --> 00:25:04,836
Really?

541
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:06,838
It's before Labor Day.

542
00:25:07,339 --> 00:25:10,467
And, if people think it's our first time,
we'll get better gifts.

543
00:25:10,550 --> 00:25:14,095
Oh! FYI, we're registered
at Bloomingdale's,

544
00:25:14,179 --> 00:25:15,222
and I will judge.

545
00:25:15,305 --> 00:25:17,724
-Let's go, Michael!
-Oh God!

546
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:22,354
[Kitty exclaims, giggles]

547
00:25:22,437 --> 00:25:23,271
[chuckles]

548
00:25:26,691 --> 00:25:28,693
Well, let's just make the best of it.

549
00:25:28,777 --> 00:25:30,278
I am heading to the market

550
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:34,783
'cause I'm going to get Fritos,
Tostitos, Doritos. All the "itos."

551
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:36,493
I am back, baby!

552
00:25:42,666 --> 00:25:44,251
Son of a bitch.

553
00:25:44,334 --> 00:25:47,754
[rock music playing]

554
00:25:47,837 --> 00:25:51,550
Okay, kids, the basement is all yours.

555
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:54,344
Lights on, shirts on, and no dancing.

556
00:25:54,427 --> 00:25:55,512
[Leia laughs]

557
00:25:55,595 --> 00:25:58,139
No dancing.
You're like the guy from <i>Footloose.</i>

558
00:26:00,433 --> 00:26:01,476
No dancing, you guys.

559
00:26:02,644 --> 00:26:06,481
Babe, you can fit three of your basements
in this basement.

560
00:26:07,399 --> 00:26:09,526
That sounds like a lot of work, Nik.

561
00:26:09,609 --> 00:26:11,319
Let's just use <i>this </i>basement.

562
00:26:13,196 --> 00:26:15,073
Don't you love all this old furniture?

563
00:26:15,156 --> 00:26:18,577
Yeah, all we need are some throw pillows
and a tetanus shot.

564
00:26:19,077 --> 00:26:22,956
Mrs. Forman, your home is so warm
and inviting.

565
00:26:23,039 --> 00:26:26,710
I mean, I can't wait to spend
all summer inside of it. [chuckles]

566
00:26:28,253 --> 00:26:29,921
What is wrong with you?

567
00:26:32,340 --> 00:26:33,592
Anyway… Okay.

568
00:26:33,675 --> 00:26:39,681
Now, if you kids get bored, I found
some old records and games of your dad's,

569
00:26:39,764 --> 00:26:43,018
and a few magazines
that I don't think he wanted me to see,

570
00:26:43,101 --> 00:26:44,561
but I got rid of them.

571
00:26:44,644 --> 00:26:45,812
They were all redheads.

572
00:26:45,895 --> 00:26:47,689
[scoffs] He sure has a type!

573
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:50,734
Anyhoo, you guys have fun.

574
00:26:54,487 --> 00:26:57,824
Whoa, this must be from a Nintendo Zero.

575
00:27:01,202 --> 00:27:02,454
No way.

576
00:27:03,330 --> 00:27:05,206
Your grandma just hooked us up.

577
00:27:05,790 --> 00:27:07,334
-No way.
-Hell yeah.

578
00:27:07,417 --> 00:27:08,627
Totally.

579
00:27:08,710 --> 00:27:09,628
[laughs]

580
00:27:10,253 --> 00:27:11,087
What is it?

581
00:27:11,796 --> 00:27:14,132
Best summer ever!

582
00:27:14,215 --> 00:27:15,550
[all laughing]

583
00:27:15,634 --> 00:27:16,843
Sign me up!

584
00:27:18,094 --> 00:27:19,596
But seriously, what is it?

585
00:27:22,265 --> 00:27:23,391
[rock music playing]

586
00:27:23,475 --> 00:27:24,517
<i>One, two, three, four!</i>

587
00:27:24,601 --> 00:27:28,813
It's the summer. Let's have fun.
We should do whatever we want. Right?

588
00:27:28,897 --> 00:27:29,981
Wrong.

589
00:27:30,065 --> 00:27:32,442
-[Leia] You know what I want?
-Don't say Jay.

590
00:27:32,525 --> 00:27:33,526
Jay.

591
00:27:34,778 --> 00:27:37,947
-You are banned from this house. Get out.
-No!

592
00:27:38,531 --> 00:27:41,576
Donna, it's Kitty!
Your daughter is about to have sex!

593
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:42,535
Where is she?

594
00:27:42,619 --> 00:27:45,080
Wait, so Dad wasn't as smooth
as he says he was?

595
00:27:45,747 --> 00:27:47,415
Let's just say you're lucky you exist.

596
00:27:47,916 --> 00:27:49,793
Hey, which one of you yelled at my kids?

597
00:27:49,876 --> 00:27:52,170
I don't know which ones are yours,
but they deserved it.

598
00:27:52,253 --> 00:27:54,089
That's Gwen and Nate, and thanks.

599
00:27:54,172 --> 00:27:55,965
I was pregnant with him for ten months.

600
00:27:56,049 --> 00:27:58,635
The doctor said it was okay,
but I don't think it was.

601
00:27:58,718 --> 00:28:02,263
I think you might be having
a reaction to one of my Lip Smackers.

602
00:28:02,764 --> 00:28:03,682
Really?

603
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:08,103
-I want to come out to your grandmother.
-I have an interview tomorrow.

604
00:28:08,186 --> 00:28:11,439
-[Nikki] Do you have any references?
-Oh, my bosses all loved me.

605
00:28:11,523 --> 00:28:12,482
But they are dead.

606
00:28:12,982 --> 00:28:15,068
[rock music continues]

607
00:28:15,151 --> 00:28:17,237
[Ozzie] I'm gaaaay!

608
00:28:18,780 --> 00:28:19,948
I said, good day.

609
00:28:20,031 --> 00:28:21,533
[all cheering]

610
00:28:22,325 --> 00:28:24,244
[rock music playing]

